  "script": "Eight goats versus one county? In Ohio, sheriff's deputies got called out for the least intimidating emergency imaginable: a herd of 8 goats loose on the road. Easy, right? Round them up, go home. Except these goats did not get the memo. As deputies closed in, one goat sized up the situation, spotted a parked SUV, and leapt clean onto the hood — then used it as a launchpad to escape. A getaway. Off a car. By a goat. The rest of the herd scattered while one four-legged mastermind disappeared down the road. Deputies eventually corralled most of them. Most. So who taught one Ohio goat to use a parked SUV as a getaway ramp?",
